Food is horrible!! I've been getting food from here for the last couple years and in the beginning it was so good (used to be my go-to spot in Harlem for good Jamaican food)but now last 6-7 months have been horrible. I'm not sure if they got a new cook but the food just isn't the same. The rice is either not cooked properly or got a burnt taste. If you order oxtails or curry goat they give you mostly bone and with very few meat. I had to write a review today because I just sent my bf to get me a small order of curry goat with rice and peas which was HORRIBLE!! let me start off my saying im Jamaican and there should be no reason the goat is red in the middle or under cooked. I opened my plate of food which was drenched in curry goat gravy which made it look like there was a lot but when i started eating it, the meet was under cooked and i only had about 3 pieces with meat and the rest was all bone and sauce. On top of that, the rice and peas was nasty. taste burnt. Wishing i would of just got white rice instead or my whole order replaced. VERY DISAPPOINTING. this place has changed their sign so much, im starting to think maybe its no longer ran by rusty.
